commit.message:
Declare separate args for intf and impl in ppx_deriving_show

Signed-off-by: Nathan Rebours <nathan.p.rebours@gmail.com>
drop the `result` compatibility package dependency

Remove extensions from fold, iter and map plugins

These don't seem very useful:
1. On types without free variables, they're just identity.
2. On types with free variables, they require specially-named poly_ functions present in the scope. These are usually declared at the type declaration level of the deriver.

These also appear to be unused according to sherlocode.

Removing map avoids a superficial conflict with ppx_let.

Declare show with_path argument for interface deriver as well

Even though the argument is unused in `.mli` files as it only affects
the implementation and not the signature of the function, it used
to be accepted back when declared via `ppx_deriving.api` so we need
to keep it that way for compatibility.

Signed-off-by: Nathan Rebours <nathan.p.rebours@gmail.com>

Revert 5.3.0 release

We inadvertently introduced breaking changes there so we will
release again once they are fixed.
